text: Teretriphora is a genus of very small sea snails, marine gastropod mollusks. They are in a family called Triphoridae. == Species == Species within the genus Teretriphora include: * Teretriphora distorta (Laseron, 1958) * Teretriphora gemmegens (Verco, 1909) * Teretriphora huttoni Suter, 1908 * Teretriphora novapostrema (Verco, 1910) * Teretriphora ponderorum Marshall, 1983 * Teretriphora spica (Verco, J.C., 1909) * Teretriphora kesteveni (Hedley, 1902): synonym of Latitriphora kesteveni (Hedley, 1903) == References == * * Obis Category:Gastropods
title: Teretriphora
